Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.19,0:00:15.93,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ancient Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.73,0:00:03.09,Narration Off,NTP,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Ancient Castle."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.09,0:00:06.40,Narration Off,NTP,0,0,0,,{\be10}An ancient castle with dignity, personality,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.40,0:00:10.34,Narration Off,NTP,0,0,0,,{\be10}and a somewhat mysterious atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.34,0:00:13.10,Narration Off,NTP,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today, let's play back the case
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.10,0:00:15.93,Narration Off,NTP,0,0,0,,{\be10}which had that castle as its stage!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.72,0:00:19.77,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The flowers dance to a piano's rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.77,0:00:21.42,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Two people face-to-face are a mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.42,0:00:23.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A great adventure in an old castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.60,0:00:25.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Detective Boys go on a treasure hunt!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.60,0:00:27.49,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.49,0:00:29.48,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.48,0:00:31.91,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.29,0:02:17.79,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,"Tōbuzankei Campsite"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.52,0:02:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.63,0:02:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a nice view!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.94,0:02:32.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Come here, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.10,0:02:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why'd we have to come camping with this cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.01,0:02:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right. The kids are happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.76,0:02:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa! There's fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.11,0:02:40.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.39,0:02:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, bring out the tent, doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.60,0:02:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tent, the tent...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.60,0:02:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.69,0:02:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you did something as stupid as forgetting the tent...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.46,0:02:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.61,0:02:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you serious!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.53,0:03:02.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, what a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.12,0:03:06.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Going camping while forgetting the most important part: the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.33,0:03:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our vacation just got ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.29,0:03:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now it looks like we're lost, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.63,0:03:16.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems we're gonna have to spend the night in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.23,0:03:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.30,0:03:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe there's an inn somewhere around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! Maybe some sort of castle by the lake?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.90,0:03:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.31,0:03:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Doesn't look so ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.53,0:03:43.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.53,0:03:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a western castle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.07,0:03:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's something like this doing in the middle of the woods?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.18,0:03:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure some guy full of cash bought a foreign castle and rebuilt it stone-by-stone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.85,0:03:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.43,0:03:58.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.51,0:04:00.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.39,0:04:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious? I'm going in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.66,0:04:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Where'd you come from, brat? Entering without permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.50,0:04:10.98,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Katsuo Tabata (41)\NMamiya Family Gardener
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.98,0:04:15.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, we're not bad people or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.10,0:04:16.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.36,0:04:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we were passing nearby we saw this incredible castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we were wondering if you wouldn't mind if we could take a look...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.54,0:04:25.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go home, go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is no place for stra—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.08,0:04:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Who are these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.64,0:04:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.96,0:04:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't remember any planned visits for today...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.80,0:04:36.42,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mitsuru Mamiya (49)\NHusband to the Eldest Mamiya Daughter\N(Adopted into the family)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.42,0:04:39.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That stupid-looking geezer wants to see the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.41,0:04:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who're you calling stupid-looking?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.26,0:04:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a brilliant scientist!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.64,0:04:45.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Scientist?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.35,0:04:46.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.51,0:04:51.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am Hiroshi Agasa, a well-respected inventor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.31,0:04:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, your intelligence...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.81,0:04:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...must be far superior to us normal people's, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.78,0:04:59.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.47,0:05:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please come inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.34,0:05:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to stay in the castle for the night?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.22,0:05:06.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! We appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.70,0:05:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.30,0:05:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think the Mistress would...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.93,0:05:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell her they're friends of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.25,0:05:16.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the state my mother-in-law's in, it'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.86,0:05:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.60,0:05:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.60,0:05:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you please let me go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.93,0:05:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.38,0:05:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a big garden!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.82,0:05:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.48,0:05:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.38,0:05:33.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a black one too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.89,0:05:36.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why is it just the head?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.44,0:05:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That horse is a knight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.26,0:05:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a chess piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.15,0:05:41.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A chess piece?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.36,0:05:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's not just the one piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.33,0:05:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the lawn where you're standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.07,0:05:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's in a checkered pattern, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.19,0:05:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lawn's cut up like a chess board.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.54,0:05:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does someone here like playing chess or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.66,0:05:55.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.16,0:05:59.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've always kept this garden like this as the previous master,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.18,0:06:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Sada'aki instructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.51,0:06:10.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he too inherited it from the master before, who died 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.22,0:06:12.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The previous owner...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.07,0:06:14.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who was that man from before?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah. He's the Mistress' second husband, Master Mitsuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.56,0:06:22.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been here since Master Sada'aki died 6 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.19,0:06:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But said Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.50,0:06:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She died in a big fire, four years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.17,0:06:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A big fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, look there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.87,0:06:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see the burned tower. That's where the Mistress slept.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.58,0:06:43.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She'd just returned to celebrate her mother's birthday...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.97,0:06:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She arrived at midnight, and before dawn, the fire'd already taken over the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.06,0:06:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And not just her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.93,0:06:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Several friends she invited,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:07:00.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the staff who served her mother for years...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.02,0:07:02.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About ten people perished among the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.25,0:07:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only ones who made it were people like me, who'd just been hired,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.91,0:07:12.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,her mother, who'd been in another room due to a cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.91,0:07:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Mitsuru, since he'd arrived just before the Mistress
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.14,0:07:22.92,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,and the Mistress and Master Sada'aki's only son, Master Takahito.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.32,0:07:28.64,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)}Takahito Mamiya (25)\NMamiya Family's Eldest Daughter's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.83,0:07:28.64,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He arrived two or three days before the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.64,0:07:35.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From what I understand, he was educated abroad, so it was our first time meeting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.64,0:07:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was also the first time we saw Master Mitsuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Mistress apparently married him abroad, and they'd been living there for all that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.61,0:07:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And for some reason, ever since the big fire, Master Takahito has lived here with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.78,0:07:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I have a feeling he's obsessed with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.25,0:08:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I imagine they weren't accepted into the castle all that well, since nobody even knew their face.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.09,0:08:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. The Mistress sent us photos from when she re-married,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.27,0:08:12.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we all knew how Master Mitsuru looked.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.39,0:08:15.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as for Master Takahito, just look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.14,0:08:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His face is the spitting image of his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.92,0:08:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, anyone seeing this can tell they're related.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.56,0:08:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what are the other paintings?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.68,0:08:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Sada'aki and the Mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.99,0:08:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Sada'aki was adopted into the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.05,0:08:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he had a lot of respect for the owner before him, as they were both historians.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.74,0:08:41.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the Mistress was jealous and always criticized him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.57,0:08:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father was just an argumentative egghead who did nothing but complain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.75,0:08:46.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.37,0:08:48.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.38,0:08:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should've been angry by my words,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.86,0:08:58.22,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)}Masuyo Mamiya (83)\NHead of the Mamiya Family
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.24,0:08:58.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he was happy that I was honest about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.22,0:08:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.75,0:09:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to bring back bad memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.87,0:09:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.19,0:09:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've gotten used to him not being in the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.07,0:09:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like when they changed the size of the passport, or the faces in the bills
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.06,0:09:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's odd at first,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.06,0:09:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but with time, you come to understand that everything changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.04,0:09:24.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Time is a terrible thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.72,0:09:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it erases both happy and sad times.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.01,0:09:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.01,0:09:34.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.72,0:09:36.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.69,0:09:40.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A scientist friend of the Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.15,0:09:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A scientist?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.90,0:09:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then they can uncover the mystery that he hid in this castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.71,0:09:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.19,0:09:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Master said it in his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.94,0:10:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he would leave his greatest treasure to the first one who solved the mystery of the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.37,0:10:06.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, is my daughter home yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.72,0:10:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was supposed to come today to celebrate my birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.02,0:10:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.38,0:10:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistress...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.40,0:10:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell her to come to my room once she arrives. I'm looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.22,0:10:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since the fire, she's been a bit senile...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.98,0:10:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Post-traumatic shock, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.43,0:10:26.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.69,0:10:30.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any room from which you can see the whole chess board?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.15,0:10:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chess board in the garden?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.09,0:10:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.20,0:10:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chess pieces are all neatly lined up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.66,0:10:40.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where? I don't see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.57,0:10:42.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't push, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.79,0:10:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see them from this room, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.17,0:10:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.80,0:10:56.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Does the pieces' layout mean anything, or...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.76,0:10:59.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're happy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.04,0:11:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's one of those codes you love so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.53,0:11:04.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.49,0:11:06.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I think so, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.73,0:11:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.17,0:11:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing!? You're gonna fall!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.40,0:11:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those morons!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.99,0:11:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.85,0:11:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I was gonna fall...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.36,0:11:23.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now he fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.55,0:11:25.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.92,0:11:26.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.66,0:11:29.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The window's right next to the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.19,0:11:33.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but in the other room, it was too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.28,0:11:38.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then what's between the two windows?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.23,0:11:57.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After all, since the old times it's been said...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.29,0:12:00.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...just match up the clock's hands and...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.41,0:12:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.79,0:12:07.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was here just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.74,0:12:10.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.49,0:12:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This ain't no normal castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.16,0:12:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is starting to get interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.76,0:12:20.32,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A staircase...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:23.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is pretty deep...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.18,0:12:25.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Where do these stairs continue to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.06,0:12:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.61,0:12:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.53,0:12:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't he in the other room just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.24,0:12:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.24,0:12:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I looked the other way, and suddenly he was gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.01,0:12:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:51.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The chair fell down and the books are scattered...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.92,0:12:54.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the clock's lid is open...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.18,0:13:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.46,0:13:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.13,0:13:14.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't do bad things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.90,0:13:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the kids do something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.32,0:13:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, just a little prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.69,0:13:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.52,0:13:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} disappeared, so we're trying to find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.37,0:13:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.33,0:13:29.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must've gone to the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.38,0:13:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's right under here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.23,0:13:33.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.18,0:13:36.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was going to the toilet, he should've told us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.64,0:13:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ugh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.71,0:13:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.18,0:13:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nobody here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.27,0:13:47.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any other toilet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.27,0:13:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place isn't used that much, so just this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.39,0:13:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he hid somewhere and wants to scare us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.31,0:14:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has to be that. Sometimes Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} can be so childish...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.74,0:14:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.01,0:14:04.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You're children too...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.49,0:14:07.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Takahito, dinner's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.44,0:14:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's dinner time already?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.95,0:14:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had them make dinner for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.02,0:14:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Want to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.77,0:14:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eel?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.67,0:14:18.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if we don't look for Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.38,0:14:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.03,0:14:23.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll probably come out when he's hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.80,0:14:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the food!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.86,0:14:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it nice sometimes for it to be cheerful like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.52,0:14:37.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since my mother died, less and less people come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.35,0:14:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did you two move here after the fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.32,0:14:48.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd long planned to come live here after I was done with the university.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.80,0:14:55.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was worried about my mother-in-law, since she lost her only daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.56,0:15:01.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I've come to love the castle my wife was born in more and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.25,0:15:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you like isn't the castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.26,0:15:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's the treasure hidden somewhere inside it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.47,0:15:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandmother...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.22,0:15:12.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.83,0:15:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't deny that my father-in-law's will {\i1}does{\i0} influence my being here...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.06,0:15:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmph. It's hard to believe my daughter could fall for such a greedy man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.11,0:15:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go eat in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.10,0:15:30.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When my daughter arrives, tell her to meet me there. I have much to tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.53,0:15:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As usual, Grandmother acts as if Mother was still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.52,0:15:38.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that her memory's bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.22,0:15:43.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since she broke her legs ten years ago, she never left the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.75,0:15:47.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, have you solved the mystery, Agasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.21,0:15:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.95,0:15:51.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? You haven't heard about it yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.18,0:15:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father said he'd leave his greatest treasure to the first one to figure the mystery of the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.44,0:16:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I heard about that from the gardener, Tabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.44,0:16:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't even know where to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.09,0:16:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chess pieces in the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.45,0:16:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that chess board was arranged by the same person who hid the treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.97,0:16:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then the position of the pieces must be a hint to find the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.46,0:16:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.71,0:16:25.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you have figured out their meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.78,0:16:28.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.94,0:16:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't solve it even though you've had four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.34,0:16:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one who could do it is lost somewhere in the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.35,0:16:39.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That mystery gourmet full of vigor and curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.87,0:16:41.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.08,0:16:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.35,0:16:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...gourmet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.77,0:16:46.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here. Will this do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.54,0:16:47.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.02,0:16:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you want that bag for?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.24,0:16:55.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to save one of my pieces of bread for Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.35,0:16:59.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll be hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.50,0:17:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, what happened to the boy with the glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.56,0:17:06.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't seen him in quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.07,0:17:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll set out to find him once we finish dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.98,0:17:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This castle's kind of like a maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.88,0:17:15.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he got lost somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.52,0:17:18.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just hope he didn't end up in that tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.43,0:17:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"That tower?"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.64,0:17:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, that tower to the left of the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.43,0:17:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's covered in vegetation ever since my wife burned to death in it, four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.77,0:17:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Also, two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.97,0:17:39.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,an employee we'd just hired mysteriously disappeared one night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.62,0:17:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking about him, it seems that he used to say that there was something
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.35,0:17:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,odd about that tower to the employees he was close to,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.25,0:17:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and so we searched for him there,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.32,0:17:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and though there were signs someone had been there recently, we couldn't find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.59,0:17:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterward we called the police, and they began a big search of the entire woods...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.05,0:18:00.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what happened after?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.44,0:18:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ten days later...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.42,0:18:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was finally found in the woods...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.48,0:18:07.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...having died from starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.08,0:18:10.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.92,0:18:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.92,0:18:15.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police concluded that he'd gotten lost in the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.83,0:18:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in an unfortunate accident, but among the staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.29,0:18:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a mysterious rumor was told for quite a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.79,0:18:30.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the souls of those that died in the tower had possessed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.34,0:18:34.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since then, the entrance to the tower is sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.30,0:18:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we have to hurry and find Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} before he starves!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.01,0:18:41.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll save my bread for him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.52,0:18:42.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.97,0:18:47.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, let's split into groups and find him before it's too dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.69,0:18:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.90,0:18:51.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.69,0:18:54.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're hiding, come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.95,0:18:58.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He doesn't seem to be in the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.27,0:19:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We looked for him inside the castle, but we couldn't find him anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.87,0:19:04.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he might be in that tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.29,0:19:05.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.50,0:19:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We checked the entrance just now,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.50,0:19:10.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the door is still locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.09,0:19:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then all that's left is the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.55,0:19:16.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's raining pretty hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.36,0:19:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Entering the woods at night is dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.17,0:19:23.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may be wiser to wait until the morning, then have the police search for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.52,0:19:26.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, you guys, get back to your rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.62,0:19:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.12,0:19:31.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.25,0:19:33.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.57,0:19:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.57,0:19:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about Edogawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.46,0:19:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not a weak man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.16,0:19:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He can find a way out of wherever he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.98,0:19:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of crying, how about you tie that bag so the bread doesn't get wet from the rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.84,0:19:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.68,0:19:54.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're going to catch a cold!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.55,0:19:56.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.44,0:19:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.50,0:20:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} so well?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.63,0:20:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.65,0:20:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.77,0:20:09.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you {\i1}like{\i0} Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.54,0:20:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.17,0:20:21.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.17,0:20:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.43,0:20:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't see him that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.40,0:20:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.54,0:20:34.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez. Kids these days... {more literal: "Kids are such trouble..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.97,0:20:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's as you say, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.\NShin'ichi's probably all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.02,0:20:46.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As they say, "no news is good news."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.19,0:20:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You actually bought that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.65,0:20:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you really think he'd let us worry for so long without contacting us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.12,0:20:58.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something happened to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.78,0:21:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe somebody in this castle kidnapped him, and he can't find a way out,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.32,0:21:05.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,or in the worst-case scenario...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.52,0:21:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.24,0:21:10.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, we have to call the police without the owners of the castle finding out,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.23,0:21:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and continue investigating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.59,0:21:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. We have to search for him, not in the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.75,0:21:21.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but inside the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.60,0:21:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I have an idea where to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.68,0:21:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Snap out of it, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.72,0:21:32.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With him gone, you're the only adult we can count on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.02,0:21:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.76,0:21:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Phone... phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.20,0:21:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.96,0:22:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Shin'ichi's cap!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.05,0:22:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with this door?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.17,0:22:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.35,0:22:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doctor? If you're going to call someone, call someone who knows us
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.66,0:22:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,like Officer Yokomizo, or Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.06,0:22:27.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.42,0:22:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doctor...?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.77,0:24:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Into the darkness of the castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.78,0:24:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,her friends disappear one-by-one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.20,0:24:07.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Detective Boys are in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.98,0:24:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.90,0:24:17.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Next Conan's Hint: Passport
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.92,0:24:24.03,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.93,0:24:19.74,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Of course, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} has one too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.74,0:24:21.37,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Eh? What?
